		<div class='e-content p-name p-summary'><p>There are plenty of sites out there (e.g. about.com) who download wikipedia&#8217;s contents wholesale and put their own adverts on it.  The advertising isn&#8217;t polluting the content (which is the main asset), it&#8217;s on wikipedia&#8217;s hosting and presentation of the content which costs real money.  Anyone is still free to download the whole lot and present it how they like.  And this facility will continue to cost money.  So I&#8217;d support advertising on wikipedia (because I wouldn&#8217;t  see &#8216;em anyway :) ).</p>
</div>
