		<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1 p-comment h-entry" id="comment-70321">
				<div id="div-comment-70321" class="comment-body">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
			<img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/0965dc1dc8c0b347e0d6525feb80394c?s=32&amp;d=identicon&amp;r=G' class='u-photo avatar avatar-32 photo' height='32' width='32' />			<cite class="fn"><a href='http://frobnosticate.com' rel='external nofollow' class='u-url url'>TM</a></cite> <span class="says">says:</span>		</div>
		
		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a href="http://gondwanaland.com/mlog/2007/01/02/wikipedia-advertising/#comment-70321">
			2007-01-03 at 7:50</a>		</div>

		<div class='e-content p-name p-summary'><p>I do not support advertising on wikipedia.</p>
<p>Whether your adblocker will intercept them is moot. The question is, as always with any form of advertising, how beholden do you want to be to funding which could be pulled if the advertisers object to your content? You lose your objectivity immediately.</p>
<p>I wouldn&#8217;t trust anything said on Wikipedia about any entity that was advertising there, and there are far too many hidden subsidiaries and trails to follow to determine whether advertiser X has an interest in WP topic Y. It would demolish the whole idea of a neutral information source. For me, anyway.</p>
</div>
		<div class="reply">
					</div>
				</div>
		</li><!-- #comment-## -->
