		<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1 p-comment h-entry" id="comment-70382">
				<div id="div-comment-70382" class="comment-body">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
			<img alt='' src='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/beb21939f6a5a1e3b48faa2d5eed358a?s=32&amp;d=identicon&amp;r=G' class='u-photo avatar avatar-32 photo' height='32' width='32' />			<cite class="fn">Anonymous</cite> <span class="says">says:</span>		</div>
		
		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a href="http://gondwanaland.com/mlog/2007/01/02/wikipedia-advertising/#comment-70382">
			2007-01-03 at 9:47</a>		</div>

		<div class='e-content p-name p-summary'><p>I think ads in wikipedia would be a very bad idea for two reasons:</p>
<p>1.Adblock: ads would not be effective, and might alienate wikipedia users that do not/can not use ad blocking software.</p>
<p>2.Forking: should ads be added to wikipedia, there&#8217;s nothing that prevents others from taking the database and forking the project. Users will tend to migrate to the new,  ad-free wikipedia, harming the project.</p>
<p>Remember: the client decides what is shown on his screen, you should consider ads a &#8220;suggestion&#8221; for the browser. Should wikipedia try ads, it would be a battle that it cannot win, and it would bother users.</p>
</div>
		<div class="reply">
					</div>
				</div>
