				<div id="div-comment-70460" class="comment-body">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
			<img alt='' src='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/d7ebeee687bd06e18381897348db9148?s=32&amp;d=identicon&amp;r=G' class='u-photo avatar avatar-32 photo' height='32' width='32' />			<cite class="fn">Muxec</cite> <span class="says">says:</span>		</div>
		
		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a href="http://gondwanaland.com/mlog/2007/01/02/wikipedia-advertising/#comment-70460">
			2007-01-03 at 15:15</a>		</div>

		<div class='e-content p-name p-summary'><p>I conditionally support ads on wikipedia.</p>
<p>1. There should be no graphical advertising, just plain text banners like AdSense, or even AdSense itself.</p>
<p>2. All users, even unregistered, should have an option to disable ads. In such case their decision is stored in cookies, indeed. The process of disabling must not take more than one click on the page where users sees the ad.</p>
<p>3. Well defined and transparent spending policy. The fate of the money must decided before the arrival of extra money and should be well known to contributors. It can be used to upgrade hardware, expand wiki staff, support FSF or EFF, buy OLPCs for poor kids, but it must be well defined and prioritized.</p>
</div>
