				<div class="comment-author vcard">
			<img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/02c60d330d903f4d07da8e90f1244e09?s=32&amp;d=identicon&amp;r=G' class='u-photo avatar avatar-32 photo' height='32' width='32' />			<cite class="fn">Ashok</cite> <span class="says">says:</span>		</div>
		
		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a href="http://gondwanaland.com/mlog/2007/01/02/wikipedia-advertising/#comment-108691">
			2011-12-19 at 2:33</a>		</div>

		<div class='e-content p-name p-summary'><p>I strongly support idea of ads on wikipedia. I have donated couple of times in the past and cannot make this as subscription every time. There was a banner that portrays the current donation scale that reaches close to 6 million and was there for almost a month and half. If they could enable that space for ads then it would have reached in few days the same amount. </p>
<p>As a end user who craves for information never mind to have some ads on one side of the site, which would help the site to sustains and grow as big as google day by day and I would enjoy more free services as google provides.</p>
</div>
		<div class="reply">
					</div>
				</div>
		</li><!-- #comment-## -->
		<li class="pingback even thread-even depth-1 p-comment h-entry" id="comment-112898">
				<div id="div-comment-112898" class="comment-body">
